        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">I've seen arguments about what race/class is allowed to use a weapon that determines what weapons a pet will wield. Personally I've always thought it was a "nerf". </P><P>If the delay of a weapon doesn't affect the pet then we would give the pet high damage high delay weapons. The pet would now be as powerful as he was with low delay daggers when he was affected by delay. Example: I have two weighted axes I got from BW. From memory the stats are something like 45/150. Sucky weapon in the hands of a PC but if a pet who wasn't affected by delay duel wielded them he'd do insane damage. I've never played a melee char so I don't know how it works, but he'd do something like......quad for 100s maybe? So my personal non-scientific theory is that the pet won't wield weapons that do over a given damage.</P><P>Paynne Nsuffering of the 56th plague - EMarr<BR>"Ask for me tomorrow and you will find a grave man"<BR><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
