        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">As I recall the damage a pet does with a weapon is 2x the weapon damage. If this damage is below what the pet hits for without a weapon, then the pet will just do regular damage. So if you give your pet a weighted axe with a damage of 45, then bam Goner is quading for 90 and VI prob dont like that. This is prob why Pet east most weapons. <BR>Personally, whenever i am in the Rath mts I go and wack Gorlin the Wicked. He drops Woe every time and its a great pet weapon, if you plan on soloing one spot for a long time. It procs 90dd and 150 poison dot i think. </P><P>Veesh</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
